OL,3,CMum's warning over super-strength drug
OL,4,Cwhich killed her son
OL,6,FShe said: "They're incredibly
OL,7,Fdangerous. We should be far more
OL,8,Fworried than anyone is at the moment.
OL,9,FI am astounded why it's taken so long
OL,10,Ffor the word to get out there. It
OL,11,Fshould be on everyone's lips.
OL,13,F"Why is it not in government
OL,14,Fcampaigns, letting people know just
OL,15,Fhow dangerous it is? And what you need
OL,16,Fto counteract that should you come
OL,17,Facross someone who's had it. In
OL,18,Fschools, in colleges, in universities,
OL,19,Fit should be aimed everywhere. It
OL,20,Fshould be out there everywhere
OL,21,Fdefinitely."
