OL,6,FThe rise in nitazene deaths has also
OL,7,Fprompted calls for more people to be
OL,8,Fprepared to save someone's life who
OL,9,Fhas taken them.
OL,11,FNaloxone is a drug which reverses the
OL,12,Feffect an opiod overdose has on the
OL,13,Frespiratory system.
OL,15,FIt comes in the form of injection or a
OL,16,Fnasal spray and is carried by many
OL,17,Fpolice officers across the UK.
OL,19,FBut charities say a wider range of
OL,20,Fpeople should be able to administer
OL,21,Fthe drug.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/9
